      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The foundational pillars of sophistication for a global professional are largely rooted in Western culture, particularly in the US and UK. You'll want to master the art of dressing conservatively yet stylishly, avoiding anything too flashy or attention-seeking. In a boardroom setting, it's essential to maintain eye contact, use assertive yet polite language, and avoid fidgeting or crossing your arms. When engaging in professional conversations, it's crucial to be well-versed in the latest industry trends and able to articulate your thoughts in a clear, concise manner. And of course, a firm handshake and a smile are still the gold standard for making a good impression.",
